The paper discusses the use of atomic swaps, which are a cryptographic protocol, to create overcollateralized debt instruments. This falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of blockchain technology, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and distributed ledger technology (cs.DLT). The paper also discusses the use of bidding processes, which falls under the category of game theory and economics (cs.GT) and financial technology (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of smart contracts, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
